        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued April 29 at 3:37PM CDT until April 30 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High risk of rip currents. Minor coastal flooding possible
around high tides cycles.

* WHERE...Gulf-facing beaches, including the Matagorda
Peninsula, Brazoria County beaches, Galveston Island and the
Bolivar Peninsula.

* WHEN...Through Wednesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water. Elevated tides could lead to
minor flooding of beaches, lots, parks, and roads with only
isolated road closures possible. This includes the lowest
more-prone spots like HWY 87/124 along the Bolivar Peninsula,
Western Galveston Island, Bluewater Highway and Surfside.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
